<subSubSection id="67F6E8BA14D2DFCC17075EE92F6921EE" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="35" pageId="17" pageNumber="34" type="type species">
<paragraph id="F121C1B0861C5BC5B9EB78B2D2ADC4C2" pageId="17" pageNumber="34">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="76A846FBEC6D6B901B8E2A3EC0AA1434" pageId="17" pageNumber="34">
<taxonomicName id="0FC2388BA04FFDA9B8F6446F452B31B4" authorityName="Gory" authorityYear="1841" class="Hexapoda" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavimana">
<emphasis id="34267BD8D16BEEB7E6ACF434497FA699" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="34">Anthaxia flavimana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gory, 1841 (subsequent designation: 
<bibRefCitation id="D64F3296CEA82DED84F7BEF1D1EEAB3B" author="Chamberlin, WJ" journalOrPublisher="Folia Heyrovskyana" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" refId="B18" refString="Chamberlin, WJ, 1926. Catalogue of the Buprestidae of North America north of Mexico. Chamberlin WJ, Corvallis, Oregon, 289 pp &amp; 1 page index." title="Catalogue of the Buprestidae of North America north of Mexico. Chamberlin WJ, Corvallis, Oregon, 289 pp &amp; 1 page index." year="1926">Chamberlin, 1926</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3C1BE5E74D5227C1C8C7850A9BD61AD5" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="35" pageId="17" pageNumber="34">
According to 
<bibRefCitation id="12C0105A3A2A28939AEDB6AA6C29D48B" author="Bellamy, CL" journalOrPublisher="Folia Heyrovskyana, Supplementum" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" refId="B3" refString="Bellamy, CL, 2008. A world catalogue and bibliography of the jewel beetles (Coleoptera: Buprestoidea). Volume 3. Buprestinae: Pterobothrini through Agrilinae: Rhaeboscelina. Pensoft series faunistica No. 78, Sofia - Moscow, pp. (1-2) + 1261-1932." title="A world catalogue and bibliography of the jewel beetles (Coleoptera: Buprestoidea). Volume 3. Buprestinae: Pterobothrini through Agrilinae: Rhaeboscelina. Pensoft series faunistica No. 78, Sofia - Moscow, pp. (1 - 2) + 1261 - 1932." year="2008">Bellamy (2008)</bibRefCitation>
, the genus 
<taxonomicName id="20A73C4A326C454D1367E9132B9E9D4C" authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1903" class="Hexapoda" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilaxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3851900C993B5EDFA6ED3D0D317AF7EA" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">
<pageBreakToken id="7DB2C02C8EF04436F3CF130E68D71000" pageId="18" pageNumber="35" start="start">Agrilaxia</pageBreakToken>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comprises 88 species. After removing of 5 species from 
<taxonomicName id="1D2CFB044661FACA44A86A4B6499E5B6" authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1903" class="Hexapoda" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilaxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="780A952377F7E9D4580E34D24BDCD155" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Agrilaxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="F5434CF6890866DFDB20F9B674268734" authorityName="Holynski" authorityYear="1989" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Bilyaxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="25193256C97C75DCDE305FED7FD91A59" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Bilyaxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see below) and after transferring of 5 species into the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="8C0443D2E4197444BD3277F1A45EFE2D" authorityName="Bily" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Costiptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D303A054AD080E57DF65E8ACDC988E40" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Costiptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgen. n., 78 species remain in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="96052B4ED94BC071C64B813F353B0CFB" authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1903" class="Hexapoda" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilaxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="77510D153762F607B6EE15F2003ACC1B" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Agrilaxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s. str. Quite naturally the subgenus will have to be split into several (or many) species-groups since several very different morphotypes (e.g. 
<figureCitation id="C6C1D9C7A28B70609CDC0C09566D74A4" captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. 1 Anthaxita peruviana, sp. n., female holotype, 5.4 mm 2 Charlesina mrazi mrazi (Obenberger, 1932), male lectotype, 6.2 mm 3 Cobosina willineri (Cobos, 1972), male, 4.4 mm (Brasil, Catamarca) 4 Marikia descarpentriesi (Cobos, 1956), male, 4.9 mm (Ecuador, Pichincha) 5 Sanchezia bucki (Cobos, 1956), 7.0 mm (male holotype of Cylindrophora kafkai Bily, 1996) 6 Agrilaxia (Agrilaxia) flavimana (Gory, 1841), male, 3.8 mm (USA, Arizona)." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/21686" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Figs 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="7362A13A1F4D45768AB81C6BF550A5CB" captionStart="Figures 19–24" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 19 - 24. 19 Agrilaxia (Agrilaxia) brunneipennis brunneipennis (Kerremans, 1900), male, 4.9 mm (Argentina, Cordoba) 20 Agrilaxia (Agrilaxia) coriacea (Kerremans, 1887), female, 4.1 mm (Argentina, Misiones) 21 Agrilaxia (Agrilaxia) kerremansi (Thery, 1909), female, 6.1 mm (Brasil, Jatahy) 22 Agrilaxia (Agrilaxia) montana Bily &amp; Westcott, 2005, female paratype, 6.7 mm (Mexico, Sta Catarina del Monte) 23 Agrilaxia (Agrilaxia) funebris (Kerremans, 1900), male, 4.7 mm (Argentina, Entre Rios) 24 Agrilaxia (Agrilaxia) alterna (Kerremans, 1900), female, 5.5 mm (Brasil, Nova Teutonia)." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/21692" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">19</figureCitation>
- 
<figureCitation id="DCA946C1C4626BCCB7FDEAE09B400B59" captionStart="Figures 25–30" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 25 - 30. 25 Agrilaxia (Agrilaxia) claudei (Cobos, 1972), female, 7.4 mm (French Guayane, Kaw) 26 Anilaroides brasiliensis (Kerremans, 1897), male lectotype (Brasil, Bahia) 27 Tetragonoschema (Tetragonoschema) undatum (Steinheil, 1874), female, 4.0 mm (Paraguay, Loma Plata) 28 Tetragonoschema (Patagoschema) patagonicum (Obenberger, 1922), female lectotype, 4.6 mm 29 Agrilaxia (Agrilaxia) decolorata (Kerremans, 1899), male, prosternum 30 Cobosina willineri (Cobos, 1972), aedeagus." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/21695" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">25</figureCitation>
) can be found within the subgenus - some of them have been suggested by 
<bibRefCitation id="2BC1D66422DBE2C1264D839FC433C8E1" author="Bily, S" journalOrPublisher="Folia Heyrovskyana" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" refId="B15" refString="Bily, S, Brule, S, in press. A study on the genus Agrilaxia Kerremans, 1903 of the French Guiana (Coleoptera: Buprestidae: Buprestinae: Anthaxiini). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae (in press)." title="A study on the genus Agrilaxia Kerremans, 1903 of the French Guiana (Coleoptera: Buprestidae: Buprestinae: Anthaxiini). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae (in press)." year="in press">
<normalizedToken id="093A54F904B6AD77ADBCF50B723E32CB" originalValue="Bílý">Bily</normalizedToken>
&amp; 
<normalizedToken id="6D2ECD93816247834CB8547E2B3D86A2" originalValue="Brûlé">Brule</normalizedToken>
(in press)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BDDD2E99B66B7031BF863ABCFD618D26" pageId="18" pageNumber="35" type="note">
<paragraph id="B259112E3978E0B74F591636BCC9B6EE" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A018057C3FBB8ED7A5892C6780B149A4" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">
The very special morphological character of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="1EEA91B3D20B50A1032B71C0824FCBEF" authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1903" class="Hexapoda" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilaxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7B0246DD36CDCC1E46DC9876C872A475" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Agrilaxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the shape of the prosternum (
<figureCitation id="A93CE09655AA46637EFB264C9C1E5B50" captionStart="Figures 25–30" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 25 - 30. 25 Agrilaxia (Agrilaxia) claudei (Cobos, 1972), female, 7.4 mm (French Guayane, Kaw) 26 Anilaroides brasiliensis (Kerremans, 1897), male lectotype (Brasil, Bahia) 27 Tetragonoschema (Tetragonoschema) undatum (Steinheil, 1874), female, 4.0 mm (Paraguay, Loma Plata) 28 Tetragonoschema (Patagoschema) patagonicum (Obenberger, 1922), female lectotype, 4.6 mm 29 Agrilaxia (Agrilaxia) decolorata (Kerremans, 1899), male, prosternum 30 Cobosina willineri (Cobos, 1972), aedeagus." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/21695" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Figs 29</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="C729125B2AE8DF953F9DB3D57EF7E00D" captionStart="Figures 31–34" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figures 31 - 34. 31 Charlesina mrazi (Obenberger, 1932), scutellum 32 the same, Anthaxita peruviana, sp. n. 33 Agrilaxia (Agrilaxia) claudei (Cobos, 1972), right protibia 34 Agrilaxia spp., anterior margin of prosternum (lateral view): (a) flat to weakly convex, (b) weakly grooved, (c) deeply grooved, (d) with sternal, longitudinal carina, (e) rolled up anterior margin, (f) peg-like spine." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/21697" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">34a-34f</figureCitation>
) which is normally flat or slightly convex. In the most species the prosternum is more or less transversely grooved just behind the anterior margin. The 
<normalizedToken id="D9B1E39CA1595965D830931543CB7C1C" originalValue="“grooving”">&quot;grooving&quot;</normalizedToken>
of the anterior portion of prosternal plate and the relative elevation of the anterior margin of the prosternum which, in the extreme case, forms a sharp, transverse, rolled up ledge which is sometimes transformed into a peg-like, medial spine (
<figureCitation id="624A0117A5ACA7AA10C07DF16042773C" captionStart="Figures 25–30" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 25 - 30. 25 Agrilaxia (Agrilaxia) claudei (Cobos, 1972), female, 7.4 mm (French Guayane, Kaw) 26 Anilaroides brasiliensis (Kerremans, 1897), male lectotype (Brasil, Bahia) 27 Tetragonoschema (Tetragonoschema) undatum (Steinheil, 1874), female, 4.0 mm (Paraguay, Loma Plata) 28 Tetragonoschema (Patagoschema) patagonicum (Obenberger, 1922), female lectotype, 4.6 mm 29 Agrilaxia (Agrilaxia) decolorata (Kerremans, 1899), male, prosternum 30 Cobosina willineri (Cobos, 1972), aedeagus." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/21695" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Figs 29</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="A1E6C957EA0EE8BCAADFEB5F7CCB01E9" captionStart="Figures 31–34" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figures 31 - 34. 31 Charlesina mrazi (Obenberger, 1932), scutellum 32 the same, Anthaxita peruviana, sp. n. 33 Agrilaxia (Agrilaxia) claudei (Cobos, 1972), right protibia 34 Agrilaxia spp., anterior margin of prosternum (lateral view): (a) flat to weakly convex, (b) weakly grooved, (c) deeply grooved, (d) with sternal, longitudinal carina, (e) rolled up anterior margin, (f) peg-like spine." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/21697" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">34f</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
